quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  104,1,"Woe to every scandalous, backbiter"
  104,2,Who accumulates wealth and counts it
  104,3,Thinking that his wealth will make him last forever
  104,4,By no means. He will surely be thrown into that which breaks into pieces
  104,5,And what will explain to you about that which breaks into pieces
  104,6,It is the fire of God kindled to a blaze
  104,7,That mounts right up to the hearts
  104,8,It will be made into a vault over them
  104,9,"In columns, extended"